President Cyril Ramaphosa says restaurants, hair salons, conference venues, casinos, and cinemas will reopen. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - More people will get back to work and will have more leisure and entertainment options after President Cyril Ramaphosa announced further relaxation of the lockdown. But all these businesses and entities will need to adhere to safety requirements. The dates when they can operate again are yet to be announced. READ: More sectors will be allowed to resume: Ramaphosa Here is a list of services that are now allowed under level three of the lockdown regulations: - Restaurants for sit-down meals - Personal care services - Conferences - Commercially licensed accommodation - Cinemas, theatres and casinos - Non-contact sport